metadata.name: Waxing Crescent #43
metadata.description:
A generator for the mascot of darkness.

The moons are generated with a real-time GAN of 1.6M parameters that has been trained on thousands of photos collected on the internet.

Each grid performs a unique cycle of 29.53 days, in sync with the iconic celestial body.

Press "r" to render the full cycle as a 2s GIF.

metadata.name: Natural order.chaos #176
metadata.description:
Generative Landscape with two possible variations, Natural order and Natural chaos. One drawn in the style of semi-realism, and the other abstract.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: Excavation #57
metadata.description:
"Excavation" reconstructs the digital screen as a thickened, palimpsestuous ground. Elements are uncovered through an archaeological survey of this ground, while others remain buried beneath layers of digital sediment.

Coded in p5.js.

metadata.name: string_pllu #17
metadata.description:
Making some abstract plants, inspired by a painting technique called string pull.

Connect some random semi circles with strings and pull the strings from the bottom of the canvas.

The semi circles rotate while moving to create some random brush strokes.

metadata.name: Zen flower card  #23
metadata.description:
Inspiration may arise in the most unimaginable places.
Harmony, however, may only spring from within.
«All the things that truly matter, beauty, love, creativity,  joy and inner peace arise from beyond the mind.»  

Pick your card from this minimalist zen flower deck to inspire you along the journey.
· 14 illustrations
· 7 colours
· Several textures & stamps.

May it find you at peace. ♡

亮福愛平
luz, bendiciones, amor, paz
light, blessings, love, peace

metadata.name: Love & Wild #131
metadata.description:
We often use flowers to express untold feelings towards our loved ones and most precious people in our life. But love as flowers can go wild & in unpredictable directions.

Love & Wild code come to life few weeks ago when I was alone drinking coffee at local bar, started messing with vertex Quadratic bezier and first petal appeared on screen. After few Loved flowers, the Wild ones start to emerge. Those with sharp spines that are beautiful in it’s own way but can also, like Love, inflict pain. As I was on vacation during finalising this work the colors and flavours of the Mediterranean inspired me.
But except some Wild palettes too.

Thank You

‘s’ for save canvas.
‘2’ for HD png.
‘4’ for 4000x4000px png.
‘8’ for 8000x8000px png.

Created with wild love for p5js and generative art :)
@Qotonana
July, 2022.

metadata.name: Morixels Colab #2 MoriCar #151
metadata.description:
We all dream of having a car or we have

Some of us even talk to our car

And some of us see our car like a cartoon character.

This collection is not only an NFT but also a match
If you win one of the cups, in addition to a Super Rare edition, there are also prizes for the owners in the Primary market, which are as follows:
The lucky winners of the Gold Cup amount to 10 Tezos
The lucky winners of the Silver Cup amount to 5 Tezos
The lucky winners of the Bronze Cup amount to 3 Tezos

The MoriCar is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 7 (78 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 3,492,720 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of the most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website 👇

Website: https://morixels.com/

Twitter: @Morixels

by: @morteza_yousefy & @ardavan_

metadata.name: hollow #126
metadata.description:
In 1993, Basque sculptor Eduardo Chillida proposed a project to create an immense void inside Tindaya, the Sacred Mountain of Fuerteventura's indigenous inhabitants. The hollow cube measuring approximately 45 x 50 x 65 meters was conceived as a space for "all the people" to "fully experience the tininess of humankind".

The idea of the project dates back to the 1980s, and it took the artist years of searching for the ideal mountain in different parts of the world. However, what was ideal for Chillida evoked a lot of controversy due to the environmental and social impact of the project. There was uncertainty about Tindaya's structural feasibility and the potential harm to the ancient petroglyphs engraved on its surface. What's more, the financial sustainability of the project's economic model would depend on hundreds of thousands of tourists visiting the site each year, converting a work of art into a holiday attraction.

Chillida called his project the Monument to Tolerance. Although it never came into existence, it has caused division and conflict since it was conceived.


"hollow" is an exploration of 256 voids in nonexistent natural monuments. Made of digital matter instead of stone and lacking cultural charge, its sole purpose is to contemplate the tininess of humankind.


-----

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the quality from preview to the resolution of a print of approximately 30cm in height. In live mode, click on PNG to save the rendered image.

Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes from a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones to render the image. 

Requirements: 1GB of RAM. The system needs up to 200 MB of free RAM for rendering square preview images and up to 400 MB of free RAM for rendering square images at the highest resolution. I tested on Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge / Windows, Mac OS, Android, and iPhone, but please make sure it works on your device before minting.

-----

Possible features:

color scheme: cairngorm, alborz, bardenas, atlas, bieszczady, watkins

proportions: square, wide, standard, narrow

frame: none, vignette, bright, dark, bright with vignette, dark with vignette

visitors: tourists, tourists and birds, solitary flock of birds, only light

metadata.name: Lime Brass Hyacinth #336
metadata.description: "Lime Brass Hyacinth" is a p5.js project where isometric shapes are placed and have their size and color adjusted based on an underlying grid of gradients. Each form is derived from the lightness or darkness of a particular pixel in the underlying grid. Many renders remind me of cityscapes with buildings, roads, and bridges.

metadata.name: Rhythms #315
metadata.description:
"Routines, patterns, cadence.
Events, turns, chaos.
Predictable lives,
split-second dramas."

This project is inspired by the delicate balance between daily habits and life-turning points.
There's structure in the flow. There's awe in the silence.

"Rhythms" invites you to reflect on the beautiful complexity that fills our vital experience, on the millions of tiny details that bring texture to our journey causing balance or disruption.

-

Key Features:
- 12 color palettes: Determines colors used on the artwork
- 3 Orientation modes (square, portrait, landscape): Portrait and landscape are rare
- 6 Alignment Types: Determines lines' distribution pattern

Secondary features provide additional variation.

Enter live mode and press "s" to download high resolution image ( 5940x5940 px ).

-

50% of secondary market royalties go to minters.
Coded in p5js, with love.

metadata.name: Unsolicited abstraction of modern times #215
metadata.description:
This piece is an abstraction and a reflection on the last era, on all that we have built and become. Are we proud of it or has it just been the result of iterating through the days? Since the technology boom, we have experienced great improvements, but perhaps also massive ...mistakes?  

Inspired by textbooks of the 80s, with elements that remind us of industry, technology, networks and systems, "Unsolicited abstraction of modern times" invites us to question our work to date. Has everything really changed?

unknowable 2022




Usage:
press [s] - save pixels (png)
press [p] - save vectors (svg)
